Short description
The progam package FEAT2D is a general purpose subroutine system for the numerical solution of partial di’¼Ćerential equations by the ’¼ünite element method. FEAT2D is designed to handle problems in two space dimensions, namely
ŌĆō Scalar elliptic boundary value problems, ŌĆō Elliptic systems of equations, ŌĆō Time dependent problems.
FEAT2D is not a user oriented system, it only provides subroutines for several main steps in a ’¼ünite element program. The user should be familiar with the mathematical formulation of the discrete problems. The data structure of FEAT2D is transparent so that modi’¼ücations or augmentations of the program package are very easy, for instance the implementation of new elements. For details in the design and data structures of ’¼ünite element codes the reader is referred to the books of Axelsson/Barker [1] and Schwarz [3], [4]. There are several main groups of subroutines in the system:
ŌĆō Generation of subdivisions of the domain Ōä” ŌĆō Assembly of global matrices related to a bilinear form a(Žåi, Žåj) ŌĆō Assembly of right hand side vectors related to a linear form l(Žåi) ŌĆō Implementation of standard boundary conditions ŌĆō Solution of the resulting linear systems of equations by iterative solvers ŌĆō Error analysis for test problems where the exact solution is known
Moreover sample programs for standard applications are included. These can be used as starting programs which can be modi’¼üed for the actual application. Most FEAT2D subroutines can be used outside FEAT2D as well since the special memory management is separated from the working program units.
