1.4. Description of the domain Ōä”

In this subsection, we explain how a two-dimensional bounded domain must be described. FEAT2D only needs information on the boundary ŌłéŌä”. It is assumed that the boundary consists of ’¼ünitely many simply closed curves which are given in parametrized form. The orientation should be chosen such that the interior of the domain is locally on the left of the boundary curves. The parameter for each boundary component starts from 0.
