In the present version of FEAT2D matrices in the storage techniques 3 (or 4 in the symmetric case), 7 (or 8 in the symmetric case) and 9 (general rectangular matrices) are supported. The routines of this group, ’¼ürst, calculate the pointer vectors, see Section 1.6, and, then, assemble the global matrices, of course using a loop over all elements. In most applications the user will only need the X-routines which also allocate the necessary arrays on the workspace vector.

