For each of the NBLOC bilinear forms to be evaluated for all basis functions there is passed the number of additive terms in the array KABN(NBLOC) and an abbreviation for the partial derivatives applied to the test (Žåi) and trial functions (Žåj) in the array KAB(2,NNAB,NBLOC). Consider, for example, the bilinear form
