The notation Žåi stands for the basis functions of the space of test functions. The conventions in the notation and parameter lists are similar to those of group A for bilinear forms. The structure of the linear form, number of additive terms and abbreviations for the partial derivatives applied to the basis functions is contained in the arrays KB(.,IBLOC) and KBN(IBLOC), for each of the NBLOC block vector separately. The coe’¼ācient function is of the form

